json.firstComment: Agile was meant for Junior developer;  Junior developer roles will  shrink greatly while “AI-team manager” jobs boom.

latestComments.text: Agile was meant for Junior developer;  Junior developer roles will  shrink greatly while “AI-team manager” jobs boom.

Agile, Waterflow were needed to help breakdown task and organize work. Project managers and scrum masters used made up deadlines to keep engineers on their toes. Work has now shifted up and right. We will not need task organizers. Might still need motivators to push engineers to think higher and go faster. Wonder what that role looks like.
As long as you've got Continuous Delivery (DORA Metrics, etc), the rest will sort itself out

Well agree do disagree. Alot of Scrum Masters and product owners are redundant and no good. Then some can actually being value.by letting the team shine and remove problems. But in the end, every coder and team gets their payment to deliver something to someone. And that someone needs to know what is being made and decide on changes. Just like the dev team needs to listen to the design requirements. The scope is often floating. And therefore some people in between is needed to manage the risks around this. And to communicate vision. There are bad people in management. And there are power ego coders that create more havoc to the team than is acceptable. And a manager is needed for that. Not seeing this is signs of socially immature profiles

New dev process framework(s) are supposed to appear. Or. If the classic dev role will be replaced with AI then developers have to move up in the food chain. The problem is that other roles would also be taken by AI. What's the fun of writing prompts about architecture and not doing architecture!? Or, let's say to figure architecture not in days and months, but hours. Then what?
Scrum meetings themselves are going to go away as the PMs and devs, QEs can use gpt tools provided by management software to figure out priorities, missing details, blockers etc

The way people lose their mind about leaps in technology is kind of incredible. AI will become something that requires maintenance and trouble shooting. In my opinion, the human element will always be required to ensure quality of production. The job will just continue to reformat.
Great thought … become Quick Developers not Agile Developer
